baby is weeks old and i'm still sad my son was born weeks and days ago i absolutely loved being pregnant i loved the feeling of my son inside of me i loved being able to take him with me wherever i went even to work i loved my big belly pregnancy was so great i also love having him and coudln't be happier but there is still this place inside of me that absolutely misses being pregnant sometimes i have to fight back tears there were stressful parts of the pregnancy but overall it was an amazing experience i even had a dream last night that i was pregnant with him again and everyone around me was touching my stomach i'm not depressed i just really miss being pregnant with him i wish it would go away i thought by this point i would forget about it and not be sad anymore but i just can't fight it and think about my pregnancy all the time what can i do to make this feeling go away that is him on my avatar and believe me he is the love of my life i couldn't be happier to have him but it's the pregnancy part that i miss so much i miss the kicks rubbing my belly and everything that went along with it and yes thank you when i do cuddle with him it's like it makes it all better breastfeeding helps a lot too but i just wish i could stop thinking about it all the time the feelings you have are totally natural i had the same problem years ago i just kept talking about the pregnancy to who ever would listen eventually the sadness will go away you can even look into a new mom's group you will really get to talk about your pregnancy and listen to other mom's experiences i can guarantee you are not alone Shaggy dog story Pregnancy EastEnders Breastfeeding Childbirth Kodocha Miscarriage Fertility awareness Charmed One Tree Hill (TV series) Cliff Richard Scenes from a Memory Kurt Cobain Abortion Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Obstetrics The Ashlee Simpson Show John Sheridan (Babylon 5) Jon Secada Friends The Inside Big Brother UK series 6 Leo